{"TopicId":55626,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Kerbin Year?","CreatedByName":"Lar-E","CreatedById":78160,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-09T11:12:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Lar-E","CreatedById":78160,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-09T11:12:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHow many days make a Kerbin year (per tracking station)?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"blizzy78","CreatedById":68543,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-09T11:29:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ll try and answer this using data from the Wiki: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Kerbin\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Kerbin\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe rotational period is 21600 sec (6 hours.) The orbital period is 9203545 sec. So that\u0027s ~426.1 Kerbin days per orbit. Since a Kerbin day is only 6 Earth hours long, that translates to ~106.5 Earth days.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lar-E","CreatedById":78160,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-09T11:42:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EBlizzy, thanks for the info, but what I\u0027m actually looking for is: when does the calendar in the Tracking Station click over to year 2, day 1? Just for mission planning purposes...\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"blizzy78","CreatedById":68543,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-09T11:50:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh, okay. That I don\u0027t know, but I\u0027m pretty sure someone else does \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Epthelyn","CreatedById":57970,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-09T11:51:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe tracking station goes by Earth time. One year is 365 Earth days, a day is 24 Earth hours etc.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAt least I\u0027m pretty sure it does, anyway.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Danish_Savage","CreatedById":49194,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-09T12:30:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt does that on day 365.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CheeseMonger","CreatedById":174835,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-13T17:17:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u0022819701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002255626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221386592201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002249194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Danish_Savage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 09/12/2013 at 0:30 PM, Danish_Savage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does that on day 365.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIncorrect! The thingy does chanvge from yar 0 to 1 at day 426\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"carlorizzante","CreatedById":144682,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-01T18:11:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222954009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002255626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487006226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174835\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CheeseMonger\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/13/2017 at 6:17 PM, CheeseMonger said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIncorrect! The thingy does chanvge from yar 0 to 1 at day 426\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue, I was looking this video today and I was wondering the same thing. You may see that a Kerbal year doesn\u0027t skip forward at 365 days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/TzXz4FzKgTQ?t=12m6s\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/TzXz4FzKgTQ?t=12m6s\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-01T18:57:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s just how you\u0027ve set it in the settings, There\u0027s a option in the settings menu to set\u00A0it to earth time (next year in 365 days) or into kerbal time (next year in 426 days).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-02T08:07:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222954009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002255626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487006226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174835\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CheeseMonger\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 13.2.2017 at 6:17 PM, CheeseMonger said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIncorrect! The thingy does chanvge from yar 0 to 1 at day 426\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222971990\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002255626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488391902\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144682\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022carlorizzante\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, carlorizzante said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrue, I was looking this video today and I was wondering the same thing. You may see that a Kerbal year doesn\u0027t skip forward at 365 days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/TzXz4FzKgTQ?t=12m6s\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/TzXz4FzKgTQ?t=12m6s\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote that this thread that \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/174835-cheesemonger/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022174835\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/174835-cheesemonger/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@CheeseMonger\u003C/a\u003E just exhumed from its grave is from 2013. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack in the days, KSP showed time only in Earth days, with 24 hours and 365 days. \u0022Kerbin time\u0022, where a day has only six hours and a year has 426 days, was added only later in the game\u0027s development. That was also when the timekeeping in general got straightened out and little inconsistencies were fixed, such as sidereal vs synodic rotation period and so on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-02T08:08:53Z\u0022 title=\u002203/02/2017 08:08  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Streetwind\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-02T08:14:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/98962-streetwind/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002298962\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/98962-streetwind/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Streetwind\u003C/a\u003E points out, lots of things have changed in the three years since \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78160-lar-e/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002278160\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78160-lar-e/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lar-E\u003C/a\u003E asked his question. But it\u0027s good we got this clarified so people can get the correct answer if they do a Good search. Well done, everyone! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ffffff;\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}